2 Model

k <- c(45,45,44,45,44,45,45,45,45,45,30,20,6,44,44,27,25,17,14,27,35,30)
p <- length(k) # number of people
n <- 45        # number of questions

data    <- list("p", "k", "n") # to be passed on to JAGS
myinits <- list(
  list(psi = c(0.7,0.5), z = round(runif(p)))) # Initial group assignment

# parameters to be monitored:   
parameters <- c("psi","z")

model_text <- "
# Malingering
model{
  # Each Person Belongs to One of Two Latent Groups
  for (i in 1:p){
    z[i] ~ dbern(0.5)
    z1[i] <- z[i]+1
  }
  
  # Bona Fide Group has Unknown Success Rate Above Chance
  psi[1] ~ dunif(0.5,1)
  
  # Malingering Group has Unknown Success Rate Below Bona Fide
  psi[2] ~ dunif(0,psi[1])
  
  # Data are Binomial with Group Rate for Each Person
  for (i in 1:p){
    theta[i] <- psi[z1[i]]
    k[i] ~ dbin(theta[i],n)
  }
}
"

samples1 <- jags(data, inits=myinits, parameters,
                 model.file = textConnection(model_text), 
                 n.chains=1, n.iter=2000, 
         n.burnin=1000, n.thin=1, DIC=T)

아래 플롯에서 빨간색 수평선은 geom_jitter()를 넣은 MCMC 표본이다. 평균은 ⊕으로 표시하였다.

f1 <- p1 %>% select(starts_with("z")) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = starts_with("z"), 
               names_to = "SID", values_to = "Value") %>% 
  separate(col = 'SID', c(NA, "Person")) %>% 
  mutate(Person = as.numeric(Person)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = Person, y = Value)) +
  geom_jitter(color = "darkred", width = 0.2, height = 0, alpha = 1/50) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks=0:1) +
  scale_x_continuous(breaks=1:22, limits=c(0.5,22.5)) +
  labs(title = expression(paste(italic(z), ": 0 - bona fide, 1 - malingering"))) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(panel.grid.minor = element_blank())

avg <- p1 %>% select(starts_with("z")) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = starts_with("z"), 
               names_to = "SID", values_to = "Value") %>% 
  separate(col = 'SID', c(NA, "Person")) %>%
  group_by(Person) %>% 
  summarise(Value = mean(Value)) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(Person = as.numeric(Person))

f1 + geom_point(data = avg, aes(x = Person, y = Value),
                size = 5, shape = 10)

위 결과에서 1~10번은 bona fide, 나머지는 malingering 참가자이다. 14~15번은 ’틀려야 한다’는 지시를 따르지 못했다.
